07/11/2003
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- The foreign ministry has rejected an invitation from Zagreb to hold bilateral talks on the controversial ecological fishing zone in the Adriatic established by Croatia before the Venice conference on the Mediterranean takes place this month. In a statement issued Thursday (6 November), the Slovene ministry said the issue was a multilateral one and suggested all Adriatic countries meet in Ljubljana after the conference. (MediaScan - 07/11/03; HINA - 06/11/03)
